---
import { Container, StickyTextImageSection } from '@components/odyssey-theme';

import Layout from '../../layouts/Page.astro';
import HomeHeroSection from '../../components/sections/heros/HomeHeroSection.astro';
import GeneralCarousel from '../../components/image-carousels/GeneralCarousel.astro';

import reindersmeer_regenboog from '/assets/reindersmeer_regenboog.jpg';
import leukermeer_luchtfoto from '/assets/leukermeer_luchtfoto.jpg';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<Layout>
	<HomeHeroSection />
	<Container>
		<section id="fotos">
			<GeneralCarousel></GeneralCarousel>
		</section>
	</Container>

	<StickyTextImageSection>
		<div slot="text-container">
			<h3>Reindersmeer</h3>

			<p>Just 400 meters from our B&B lies the beautiful Reindersmeer, near the former lock in Bosserheide in
				Well. Since 1999, this lake has been an integral part of the Maasduinen National Park. With its
				crystal-clear, azure-blue water, it evokes images of Southern Europe on sunny days and truly feels like
				a little vacation close to home.</p>

			<p>The Reindersmeer area is all about nature. The shores are dominated by a rich vegetation of heath,
				grasses, mosses, and various plant species, which contribute to the unique character of the landscape.
				The area is ideal for quiet recreation; cycling, walking, and horseback riding are favorites among
				visitors here. Swimming and fishing are not allowed to maintain the natural balance and tranquility.</p>

			<p>This lake forms an important ecological connection between the Bergerheide and the Hamert. The variety of
				flora and fauna in this area is remarkable, making it a beloved spot for nature enthusiasts and
				photographers. Several hiking routes have been marked, some of which can be shortened with a small ferry
				across the water—a fun and adventurous way to explore the lake.</p>

			<p>or birdwatchers, Reindersmeer is a paradise. The area is home to many species of waterfowl, and with a
				bit of luck, you might even spot the majestic sea eagle that occasionally hunts here. Additionally, the
				lake is surrounded by beautiful viewpoints and spots to quietly enjoy the scenery.

			</p>

			<p>Whether you're here for a relaxing walk, a bike ride through nature, or simply to pause and take in the
				serene surroundings, Reindersmeer has something for everyone. It’s a hidden gem that you shouldn’t miss
				during your stay at our B&B.</p>

		</div>
		<picture slot="image-container">
			<Image
				src={reindersmeer_regenboog}
				alt="Reindersmeer met regenboog"
			/>
		</picture>
	</StickyTextImageSection>

	<StickyTextImageSection>
		<div slot="text-container">
			<h3>Leukermeer</h3>

			<p>The Leukermeer is an ideal and popular destination for water sports enthusiasts and leisure seekers, just
				a short distance from our B&B. This versatile lake offers a wide range of activities for all ages and is
				renowned for its two beautiful marinas and inviting day beach. Whether you're an avid water sports
				enthusiast or simply want to relax by the water, Leukermeer has something for everyone.</p>

			<p>The possibilities at Leukermeer are endless. You can swim in the clear waters or test your balance with a
				paddleboarding session. For those who prefer to get out on the water, there are plenty of options for
				sailing, kayaking, or exploring the surroundings on a pedal boat. If you're in the mood for a leisurely
				boat trip, you can rent a sloop and enjoy the tranquility on the water. Leukermeer is also a favorite
				spot for anglers, thanks to its fish-rich waters and peaceful environment.</p>

			<p>Around the lake, you'll find various walking trails that invite you to take a relaxing stroll along the
				shore, where you can enjoy the beautiful view of the water. The area is perfect for a quiet day in
				nature, where you can unwind on the day beach or along the promenade. Additionally, there are several
				dining options around the lake where you can enjoy a bite to eat and a drink. With the stunning view of
				the water, this is the perfect place to unwind.</p>

			<p>Leukermeer is a place where you can enjoy both relaxation and adventure throughout the day. Whether
				you're watching the sunrise during an early morning walk, spending the day on the water, or ending the
				evening with a lakeside dinner as the sun sets—this is a place to create lasting memories. During your
				stay at our B&B, a visit to Leukermeer is highly recommended!</p>

		</div>
		<picture slot="image-container">
			<Image
				src={leukermeer_luchtfoto}
				alt="Reindersmeer with rainbow"
			/>
		</picture>
	</StickyTextImageSection>

</Layout>

<style>
    .feature-card__section {
        margin: var(--section-margin) auto;
    }

    .feature-card__grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: var(--theme-grid-gap);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .feature-card__grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }
</style>
